               <div class="btArticleContent ">
                  <div class="bt_bb_wrapper">
                  <div class="bodytext contentText"> <p>The seasons are changing and Winnipeg residents are no strangers to severe weather. Before the snowstorms hit, the Fall will bring some serious rain complete with gusts of wind and colder temperatures.&nbsp;<span style="font-weight: bold;"></span></p> </div> <div class="bodytext contentText"> <p>Most of us know what this type of severe weather can do to the exterior of our homes; but we overlook the way that it impacts our HVAC systems.&nbsp;When the mercury starts to drop and those first snowflakes hit the ground, the last thing you want is for your furnace to fail. Not only is this extremely uncomfortable, it’s also expensive. Emergency calls to your HVAC repair professional in the middle of a snowstorm come at a pretty steep price. Fortunately, the experts at East Side Ventilation have put together some tips for protecting your HVAC system against the dangers of stormy weather.</p><p><span style="font-weight: bold;"><br></span></p><p><span style="font-weight: bold;">What Can You Do to Stay Warm this Winter?</span></p><p>Making sure that you have consistent heating in Winnipeg is a priority. These are some things that you can do to get ready for oncoming storms:</p><p><br></p><ul><li>Avoid the need for mid-winter emergency heating repair in Winnipeg by taking advantage of regular HVAC maintenance. About a month before the weather turns,<a href="//<?php echo $_SERVER['SERVER_NAME']; ?>/furnace-cleaning-winnipeg" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">have a certified professional check</a> all ducts, change filters, and make sure that everything is in good working order.</li><li>Insulate your exterior pipes and ducts by wrapping them in an approved insulation sleeve.&nbsp;</li><li>If you use a tank for gas or oil, make sure that it’s adequately filled prior to inclement weather. This prevents sudden and unexpected emergency fills that can cost quite a bit more than standard services.</li><li>Move furniture and other items in the home away from vents. This allows the warm air to flow freely and better regulates the home’s temperature.&nbsp;</li><li>Keep ice from building up on exterior equipment. This can include heat pumps, AC units and any exhaust areas. Ice can weigh things down and seriously damage the inner workings of certain mechanisms.</li><li>Consider investing in an emergency generator. The longer your home has to sit in the cold, the more opportunities there are for damage to occur. Your generator also acts as a backup when the power lines go down due to wind or ice.</li><li>Don’t wait to <a href="//<?php echo $_SERVER['SERVER_NAME']; ?>/furnace-repair-replacement-winnipeg" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">repair or replace your furnace</a> or entire HVAC system. Budget for it in advance and make the necessary upgrades a couple of months prior to changing seasons.</li><li>Make sure that your walls, windows, attic, and doors are all properly insulated and water tight. There’s nothing quite as inconvenient as heat loss due to poor insulation or a leak that causes lasting water damage.</li></ul><p><span style="font-weight: bold;">A Little Prevention Saves You A Lot of Trouble</span></p><p>If you’re feeling a little overwhelmed and worried about the upcoming storm season, don’t hesitate to call the professionals at East Side Ventilation. Ask about regular yearly maintenance and set up a schedule to keep your HVAC system in excellent shape. Our certified experts can help you weather any storm with confidence, click <a href="//<?php echo $_SERVER['SERVER_NAME']; ?>/testimonials" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">here</a> to read satisfied client testimonials. For more tips on Preparing your HVAC System for the winter season <a href="/blogs/hvac-winter-checklist-winnipeg" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="link_clicked">read for more here</a>.</p><p><span style="font-weight: bold;"><br></span></p><p><span style="font-weight: bold;">Call us today at <span data-global="phone">204-667-8700</span> or <a href="/winnipeg-hvac-company-contact" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">contact us online</a> to set up a consultation or ask about our&nbsp;<a href="//<?php echo $_SERVER['SERVER_NAME']; ?>/hvac-Manitoba-hydro-financing" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">financing options</a>.</span></p><p><br></p> </div> 
